(Because in the cash flow statement adjustments a positive “increase” in a current asset is shown as a decrease in cash and vice‐versa, the figure would be shown on the “(Increase) Decrease in Interest Receivable” line as a positive number if receivables increased.)

Therefore, the answer (expressed in the format requested) is:
